author: Nexcell Pride
text:
A whole and Legendary stream ever today. :_るんるん:
The mission was... "How many diamonds (or Daiya) will be catched in 60 minutes?"
In a previous Minecraft stream with the same challenge (2020 October 26th), Rushia-daitenshi got 84 Diamonds and 9 Emeralds. Now, Rushia-daitenshi surpassed the goal, and at last moment made a clutch with a total of 116 Diamonds.
At 1:23:46 and with 97 diamonds on her own, the chronometer marked 59 minutes and 59 seconds when a miracle occured 🍀 Daiya went up from 97 to 116. 💎

Maybe Rushia-daitenshi on Minecraft would open a Diamond Mining Industry one day...
Needs some workers, but all at time... :_きゅん:

But the tense moment was the returning at home, after the Mission Accomplished. Rushia-daitenshi went lost in the "Labyrinth", but finally found the entrance/exit. Everyone was with the heart pumping out. 

And today's Supaachaato Orei Time was a quite longest, due to the Superchats at starting stream (Even at “Taiki Nanodesu” moment)
It's because 2 days without streaming, Superchats went boom. 
And the after ending, the Superchats continued flowing and Rushia-daitenshi smiled.

Wow... Personally talking, it's my return to watching from start, later of missing that utawaku and feeling bad. Now I'm so happy.
And... The crew at final 5 minutes LiveChat, thank you for solving a doubt of mine. Really I was surprised 😳❤️

text:
雷雨のため、毎日のタイムスタンプをお届けできません。私が来た時にはすでにチャレンジは終了していました。次の流れで埋め合わせをします。出来るだけ詳しく書いてみます。GTA5の記録を更新できるかどうかはわかりませんが。
Due to the thunderstorm, I can't deliver you the daily timestamps. The challenge was already finish when I came. I'll make it up to you on your next stream. I'll try to make it as detailed as I can. I'm not sure if I can break my GTA5 record.
